# Design Instructions

> **Apply Intelligently** - UI components, design tokens, and visual patterns.

## Scope

**In scope**: UI components, design tokens, visual patterns
**Not in scope**: UX flows (→ ux.mdc), brand colors (→ docs/branding.mdc)

## Design System

Wegoby uses a token-based design system. All visual values come from tokens defined in `branding/`.

### Design Tokens

| Category | Source File | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| Colors | `branding/colors.json` | `primary`, `secondary` |
| Typography | `branding/typography.json` | `heading`, `body` |
| Spacing | `branding/visual-patterns.json` | `sm`, `md`, `lg` |
| Borders | `branding/visual-patterns.json` | `radius-sm`, `radius-md` |

### Token Usage

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Use tokens
<Button className="bg-primary text-white rounded-md p-4">

// ❌ Bad: Hardcoded values
<Button className="bg-[#F4B4C0] text-[#fff] rounded-[8px] p-[16px]">
```

## Component Guidelines

### Component Structure

```
components/
├── Button/
│   ├── Button.tsx        # Component logic
│   ├── Button.test.tsx   # Tests
│   ├── Button.stories.tsx # Storybook (if used)
│   └── index.ts          # Export
```

### Component Patterns

```typescript
interface ButtonProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  children: React.ReactNode;
  onClick?: () => void;
  disabled?: boolean;
}

export function Button({
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'md',
  children,
  onClick,
  disabled = false,
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'rounded-md font-medium transition-colors',
        variantStyles[variant],
        sizeStyles[size],
        disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'
      )}
      onClick={onClick}
      disabled={disabled}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Visual Hierarchy

### Typography Scale

| Level | Use For | Token |
|-------|---------|-------|
| H1 | Page titles | `text-4xl font-bold` |
| H2 | Section titles | `text-2xl font-semibold` |
| H3 | Subsections | `text-xl font-medium` |
| Body | Content | `text-base` |
| Small | Captions | `text-sm` |

### Spacing Scale

| Size | Value | Use For |
|------|-------|---------|
| xs | 4px | Inline elements |
| sm | 8px | Tight grouping |
| md | 16px | Standard spacing |
| lg | 24px | Section gaps |
| xl | 32px | Major sections |

## Responsive Design

### Mobile-First

Always start with mobile styles, add larger breakpoints:

```css
/* Mobile first */
.container {
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* Tablet and up */
@screen md {
  .container {
    padding: 2rem;
  }
}

/* Desktop and up */
@screen lg {
  .container {
    padding: 3rem;
  }
}
```

### Breakpoints

| Name | Width | Use For |
|------|-------|---------|
| sm | 640px | Large phones |
| md | 768px | Tablets |
| lg | 1024px | Laptops |
| xl | 1280px | Desktops |

## State Styles

### Interactive States

Every interactive element needs:

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Default | Normal appearance |
| Hover | Mouse over |
| Focus | Keyboard focus |
| Active | Being clicked |
| Disabled | Not interactive |

### Loading States

```typescript
function Button({ loading, children }) {
  return (
    <button disabled={loading}>
      {loading ? <Spinner /> : children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Accessibility

### Color Contrast

- Text on background: minimum 4.5:1 ratio
- Large text: minimum 3:1 ratio
- UI components: minimum 3:1 ratio

### Focus Indicators

```css
/* Visible focus ring */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

